*Project Name: [http://www.box.net/shared/kcygnea275j4pejpm3mq Digital City project]
*Author: [http://marc.blogs.it Marc Canter] and [http://DigitalCityMechanics.com Digital City Mechanics]
*Description: The Digital City Project combines online software, community programs and multimedia projects into an environment where jobs can be created. This “digital economy ecosystem” is based upon providing free training, multimedia community content channels, entrepreneurial activities and technical support to local neighborhoods via “digital bureaus”. Community workshops, live events and online multimedia projects will be produced at these bureaus utilizing free software tools which together create a “community engagement platform”.
* Status:  After two years of research, putting on internships, supporting local community groups and networking - the '''Digital City project''' is now being customized for the Tampa Bay area.

The Digital City Project utilizes a community engagement platform which provides citizens a customizable dashboard from which they can learn, collaborate and work. Built-in real-time video support enables any dashboard user to connect to a live operator—at any time. The train-ing courseware, live events production notes and multimedia project management are all tightly coupled to the community engagement dashboard. Collaboration, media management and small biz support are all built into the platform.

==Business, Exchange and Social Commerce==

* [http://bitcoin.org Bitcoin] - p2p virtual currency, offering censorship resistance and anonymity; and based on strong encryption

* [http://ourgoods.org/ OurGoods] - barter network for the creative community

* [http://beex.org/ BEEx] - open source fundraising platform

* [http://metacurrency.org/ Metacurrency Project] - seeks to build a platform and protocol standards that will allow for multiple and interoperable currencies to exist on the Internet

* [http://www.communityforge.net/ Community Forge] - free, open source software for setting up an alternative economy

* [http://www.cminds.net Collaborating Minds] enables a diverse group of thinkers and doers from multiple fields to work effectively and enjoyably together. This platform will enable groups of people to tackle social and organizational problems that have resisted previous solution attempts. We will be more effective because we focus on explicitly fostering trust within the network, on better problem definition and structuring, and on avoiding premature leaps to conclusions. To test the platform, we are recruiting an initial community of collaborating problem solvers.  Think of it as the intersection of high-performance teams, process management, and social networks.

* How can an open project fairly share revenue and decision-making power between all of its contributors? [http://www.pietrust.com PieTrust] is an open company making a collusion-resistant reputation system. Our system allows a group to collaboratively decide how to distribute a limited quantity (such as money or voting strength) among its members. We are an open company; we invite anyone on the internet to contribute, and we will share the proceeds of our business using our own system.

